cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.NI, cs.DC 

The paper deals with the detection of coordinated cyber-physical attacks in power grids, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and control systems (cs.SY). The proposed approach involves the use of game theory (cs.GT) to minimize the defense cost, and simulations are performed using a power system simulator (cs.NI, cs.DC). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CR and cs.SY, followed by cs.AI, cs.NI, and cs.DC.
